metadata.name: Urban Flora #452
metadata.description:
Urban Flora is a generative artwork exploring interplay of natural and artificial forms created by Marcin Ignac / @marcinignac

http://marcinignac.com/projects/urban-flora/

The project was inspired by the 3/4/5G network infrastructure more and more present in the parks and greenery of our cities. Final Urban Flora transformed into a study of abandoned structures of a long forgotten civilisation.

The whole image is generative and/or procedural. Leaves are parametric, twigs and trees use the space colonisation algorithm, and the geometry is based on platonic solids transformed though series of operations.

Features determined at the time of minting:
- one of the platonic solids or a prism
- one of 15 geometry transformations
- a color theme
- leaves or detailed twigs
- leaf's spread and the amount of ridges

'g' / 'tree finger tap' - resolution and export
'drag' - rotate
'scroll' - zoom (on desktop)

Please note the project needs a decent GPU.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

--
With dedication to my wife.

metadata.name: Morixels Colab #5 Gango #136
metadata.description:
The Gango collection was created from famous western symbols so that the whole world knows it.
In this collection, you can see a combination of unrelated but beautiful components.

Try your luck to have a more beautiful combination

The Gango is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 9 (72 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 74,027,520 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of most Morixels Mans to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website üëá

Website: https://morixels.com/

by: @morteza_yousefy & @mahdirezafathi

metadata.name: Antiflow #20
metadata.description:
"Opposites are not contradictory but complementary." -¬†Niels Bohr

The concept of yin and yang is an ancient philosophy about¬†how opposing¬†forces are not only complementary but actually give rise to each other. This idea¬†reverberates through nature, art, and life itself. Now it is at the heart of modern physics. Perhaps this is a fundamental¬†law of nature baked into the¬†very fabric of existence.

Antiflow is an exploration of how balanced complexity can arise¬†from chaos by harnessing the dynamic interplay of opposing¬†forces. To that end we were inspired to create this wildly unique¬†set by mixing modern physics concepts with abstract expressionism and retro 3D primitives.

The aspect ratio¬†is 3:2 to facilitate poster size prints and device wallpapers. Results are presented without borders, noise, or other effects to allow for maximum detail. Feel free to rotate in whatever direction you choose for the best display.

Press "S" to save at a higher definition.

metadata.name: Gestalt #380
metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

Controls:
‚Ä¢ Left-click/tap reassembles the piece with one less element each time

metadata.name: One Day #8
metadata.description:
One day I will have the peace, the happiness of being able to live quietly, with comfort in peace, nature, and technology side by side. The fresh air and the fast download, the sound of birds and my GPU, a nice sofa, and the calm, cool breeze on my face nourish me to the point of forgetting all my problems. One day... One day all this will be true and only peace will be my gift.
